A recent survey in urban Shanghai revealed high obesity rates among adults and children, mirroring developed countries.
Improved living standards contribute to the rise, with lack of exercise and high-fat diets as key factors.
Men, older adults, and those with lower education levels are at higher risk.
The government aims to reduce obesity levels by 2005.
Similar concerns exist in the UK and Kuwait, where hypnotherapy shows promise.
Diabetes is a growing concern globally, with insulin availability a challenge in some regions.
Education on healthy diets and lifestyles is crucial to combat these health issues.
